#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""konjo-eval: the meta-gate eval harness CLI.

STUB (phase 1). The harness runs the gate against the eval corpus in evals/fixtures,
records detection_rate / false_positives / missed_bugs, and fails the build if the
gate regresses below the prove baseline. This is how the gates test themselves: a gate
that stops catching a known bug class is itself a defect.

Contract for the phase-1 implementation:
  konjo-eval run [--profile PATH] [--corpus DIR]
    - load each fixture (diff.patch + expect.json)
    - apply the gate, compare against expect (must_flag / must_be_silent)
    - emit a JSON report and exit nonzero on any regression vs the prove baseline

See evals/runner.py for the harness internals (also stubbed).
"""

